// JSON is a textual format for representing a collection of values:
// a simple value (string, number, "true", "false", "null"), an array of values, or an object.
// Ballerina has a single type named `json` that can represent any JSON value.
// Thus, `json` is a built-in union type in Ballerina that can contain values of the types
// nil (as the `null` value), `boolean`, `int`, `float`, `decimal`, `string`, `json[]`, and `map<json>`.
